<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-314] DistributedRowMatrix needs a sparse DistributedRowMatrix times(DistributedRowMatrix other) implementation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-314</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the matrix which is being multiplied by has been transformed into a column-sparse matrix backed by a SequenceFile&amp;lt;IntWritable,VectorWritable&amp;gt;, then doing a simple map-side join on the two, and taking the (sparse) outer product of each row-pair, and then doing a matrix-summing reducer (probably row-at-a-time, for memory constraints) would implement sparse matrix multiplication in one pass over the data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
